'''Lewis "Lew" Frankfort''' is the Chairman and CEO of [[Coach, Inc.]].<ref>[http://www.businessweek.com/bw50/2005/executive/COH.htm CEO BIO: Lew Frankfort<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>  

==Early life and career==
Frankfort was born in [[The Bronx]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Serchuk|first=David|title=Head Coach|url=http://www.forbes.com/2005/01/31/cz_ds_0131good_ls.html|work=Forbes.com|accessdate=21 July 2012}}</ref>  and holds a [[B.A.]] from [[Hunter College]] and an [[M.B.A.]] from [[Columbia Business School]].  Frankfort joined Coach in 1979 as the Vice President of New Business Development.  In this capacity, he spearheaded the development of Coach stores and its introduction into international markets.  When Coach was acquired in 1985 by [[Sara Lee Corporation]], Frankfort was appointed President of Coach.  In 1995, he was appointed Chairman and CEO.<ref>[http://www.coach.com/online/handbags/genWCM-10551-10051-en-/Coach_US/CompanyInformation/InvestorRelations/IR_ExecutiveOfficers Executive Officers<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

